<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1712,2025]" pageId="3" pageNumber="408">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1712,1737]" pageId="3" pageNumber="408">Coloration.</emphasis>
In 70% ethanol: grayish brown on dorsal and lateral surfaces of head and dorsal surface of body, dark yellow on ventral region. Pale brown on lateral surfaces of body immediately dorsal and ventral to lateral myoseptum, giving impression of two diffuse brown lines on body: one on lateral myoseptum and another along inter-dorsal region and adipose-fin base. Dorsal fin grayish brown; dorsal surfaces of pectoral and pelvic fins grayish brown, with ventral surfaces of pectoral and pelvic fins dark yellow. Anal-fin rays grayish brown, fin membrane dark yellow. Caudal fin with large irregular grayish brown spot at base; distal half of distalmost 4–5 principal fin rays grayish brown, fin membranes and remainder of fin rays dark yellow. Dorsal surface of nasal and maxillary barbels grayish brown, ventral surface dark yellow. Mandibular barbels dark yellow. Coloration in life similar, but with darker overall body color (
<figureCitation box="[640,710,2000,2025]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,559,581]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,537]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,537]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Exostoma ericinum, paratype, ZRC 56672, 97.0 mm SL. Lateral view showing coloration in life. Photograph courtesy of H Zhou." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1250937/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="408">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
